# 4. レッツ現場視察！

Emu: Alright...
Emu: Here we are! The place where we'll be pulling weeds!
Honami: So, we're going to be in charge of the area spanning from here to the grounds of that shrine over there?
Mafuyu: Yes, so let's start looking around. This may very well be the key to us finding the solution to our problems like you said, Otori.
Emu: Yeah, let's go!
Emu: (Keisuke and Shosuke are always saying how important it is to go see things for yourself when planning a new ride or event...)
Emu: (So, we have to observe things really closely, and try to come up with a way to make pulling weeds really fun!)
Emu: Oh! There's a park over there!
Honami: Oh, you're right. It's so cute and little.
Mafuyu: And it has plenty of shade, so it must be cool. We could use it as a rest area.
Emu: Rest...
Emu: Oh, I know! What if we all had lunch there?
Honami: Hehe. That's a nice idea. We could have ourselves a big picnic.
Mafuyu: Yes, we could. Our original plan was to have everyone go wherever they like, but having lunch as a group could be very fun.
Mafuyu: But, that likely won't be enough to convince people to join us. Let's keep walking around to see if we can find something else.
Emu: Okay!
Emu: Oh, I see the shrine!
Mafuyu: Yes, there it is.
Honami: Th-This shrine has a very...rustic feel to it...
Mafuyu: Yes... It looks quite old...
Emu: Oh! Look at all the crows perched up there!
Emu: Caw! Caw! Hello-caw!
Emu: Hehe♪ They greeted me back!
Honami: Th-They sound a little angry to me...
Mafuyu: Anyway, shall we keep going...? We may find something new.
Emu: Yeah! Let's keep exploring!
Honami: O-Okay...
Honami: Oh... It's so dark here. I'm starting to get a little scared...
Mafuyu: Me too. But it doesn't feel that hot here because of all the shade these trees provide.
Honami: Oh, you're right. Pulling weeds here might not actually be so bad...
Emu: Yeah! More people might come if we let them know that it's not gonna be as hot as they think!
Man: Ah, are you here to visit the shrine?
Honami: Eep! Y-You scared us...
Man: Oh, I didn't mean to startle you. It's just so rare to see anybody here at this time of day during the week.
Emu: Huh?
Mafuyu: Excuse me, but you are...?
Head Priest: Ah, where are my manners? My name is Kawada. I'm this shrine's head priest.
Mafuyu: Yes, I see. It's nice to meet you. We're all students at Miyamasuzaka Girls Academy.
Emu: We're volunteering to pull out all the weeds, so we came to see what things are like around here!
Head Priest: Ah, you're the Miya Girls students! Yes, I've heard about you.
Head Priest: Thank you very much for volunteering. I'm sure you ladies have better things to do than pull weeds at this old shrine...
Honami: N-No, it's our pleasure! I was a little surprised at first... But it's actually a very charming place, with so much greenery.
Mafuyu: I'm also glad we came. You can really feel this place's history.
Head Priest: Thank you very much. That's very kind of you to say.
Head Priest: The truth is, I'm also looking forward to you all coming to volunteer.
Emu: Huh?
Head Priest: I do my best to keep this shrine in good shape, but it doesn't get many visitors since it tends to make people feel a little uncomfortable.
Head Priest: Which is why I'm hoping that everyone who comes to volunteer will have a chance to become more familiar with this place.
Emu: Oh, I see...
Emu: (If that's the case, then I wanna recruit as many volunteers as I can for him!)
Emu: (Still, how do we do that...? It's nice and cool with plenty of greenery here, but I'm not sure how fun that makes this place...)
Emu: Excuse me!
Emu: Are there any spots in this area that you would recommend to visit?! Preferably something that everybody would enjoy!
Head Priest: Something that everybody would enjoy...?
Head Priest: I'm sorry, but there isn't really anything besides this shrine and the mountain behind it...
Emu: Mountain?
Head Priest: Yes. Actually, it's more of a large hill than a mountain. Our shrine has been watching over it for generations, and it has a similar atmosphere to the shrine itself...
Head Priest: So I wouldn't call it fun so much as scary...
Emu: (Scary...?)
Mafuyu: Is that it over there?
Head Priest: Yes. You can reach it by taking the path out back.
Emu: (Oh, all the big trees make everything look dark and spooky...!)
Emu: (Hmm... But I'm kinda interested since it looks like just the sort of place where you'd see ghosts...)
Emu: Hm...? Ghosts...?
Emu: AHHHHHH!!!
Honami: Huh...?! Wh-What's wrong, Emu?
Emu: Excuse me! If we aren't allowed to, that's okay...
Emu: But can we try doing a test of courage there?!
Mafuyu & Honami: What...?
